DTSTAMP:20260520T045949Z
DESCRIPTION:Go behind the scenes with MAP's conservation team to explore textile preservation in museums. This hands-on workshop covers museum storage and methods\, plus practical tips for safeguarding your cherished textile heirlooms at home.\nPlease note that this workshop has limited seats for two slots:\n11:00 am - 1:00 pm\n2:30 - 4:30 pm.\nRegistrations are first-come\, first-served.\nThis workshop is part of International Museum Day programming.
DTEND:20260524T110000Z
DTSTART:20260524T053000Z
SUMMARY:Caring for Textile Collections
UID:1276@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/caring-for-textile-collections/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Copy-of-DSC05127-scaled.jpg
CATEGORIES:Guided Walk,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260519T040406Z
DESCRIPTION:Dive deeper into our collection with a guided walk of our visual storage by Tanya Maheshwari and Manisha Tamilmani from the MAP Collections team\, and witness the sheer volume of art and artefacts carefully preserved.\n\nIn this session\, visitors will also understand the challenges of storage\, the importance of conservation\, and the surprising discoveries that await within our hidden spaces in the museum.
DTEND:20260524T120000Z
DTSTART:20260524T113000Z
